                <head>22. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On January 15, 1962, Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1"
                        >McNamara</persName>, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_NFEJ1"
                        >Nolting</persName>, Admiral <persName corresp="#p_FAHD1">Felt</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGLGLC1">General McGarr</persName>, and numerous other
                    officials met at <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> Headquarters in
                    Honolulu for the second Secretary of Defenseʼs Conference. A full record of the
                    meeting is in Washington National Records Center, RG 84, Saigon Embassy Files:
                    FRC 68 A 5159, SGN (62) 19-<gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>-DEFSEC-<gloss
                        target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss>. For a summary record, see <ref
                        target="#d29">Document 29</ref>. Regarding the first Honolulu Conference,
                    December 16, 1961, see <ref target="frus1961-63v01#d324">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1961–1963, volume I, Document
                        324</ref>.</p>
            </div>
